class Solution {
    public int countSegments(String s) {
        int count = 0;
        boolean inSegment = false;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) != ' ') {
                if (!inSegment) {
                    count++;
                    inSegment = true;
                }
            } else {
                inSegment = false;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Single left-to-right scan tracking whether we are inside a segment; increment count only when transitioning from space to non-space. Minimal CPU cycles and memory.

